title: For Sale:  Ultra Light Weight Survival/Camping .22 cal Pack-Rifle
postcontent:
Ultra Light Weight Survival/Camping .22 cal Pack-Rifle. Manufactured by Pack Rifle in Utah, this ultra-light weight rifle is a single shot .22 LR survival and camping rifle. The rifle breaks down into two separate pieces in less than 2 seconds to eject and reload spent cartridges and for ease of carry in even a small daypack. The receiver, and most other parts are machined from high strength aluminum.  Most wear parts and fasteners are constructed of stainless steel. The barrel is a precision button rifled, Cro-Moly liner with a carbon fiber composite outer. Carbon fiber is also used for the butt stock tube of the rifle. This construction makes the Pack-Rifle both weather resistant and the lightest rifle out there. I personally did a camouflage paint job on the rifle and made a kydex sheath for the rifle so it doesn’t get banged around too much in a pack. I have put about 100 rounds total through the rifle. I purchased the rifle from the company for $425 + tax. 
This rifle also comes with a very small 4x20 air rifle scope and mount which helps considerably with the accuracy and shooting past 30 yards. It also comes with a small fishing reel attachment system with collapsible rod extensions contained in the buttstock tube. When the rifle is broken down into its two separate parts you can use the rear half as a fishing pole. It is actually really cool to use and a nice piece of creative design. All of these accessories were designed and purchased from the company. The cost for the scope and mount was $70 + tax and the fishing rod/reel set was $90 + tax from the company.
It is a great little set up and if you are a lightweight camping/hiking enthusiast then this rifle is worth looking into. I am getting rid of it because I have stopped hiking and I am hoping another hiker and small game hunter would like to purchase it. I have attached links to a YouTube video for the rifle and accessories and if you Google Pack Rifle you can view the exact specs. I am asking for $400 for the rifle and accessories and the buyer will need to pay for the FFL fee. If you are in the Denver Metro area I will drive to meet you at just about any gun shop you like in order to do the FFL transfer.
